    <text type="note" xml:lang="ru" xml:id="letter-09013">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when-custom="1786-04-21">1786 г. апреля 21.</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Первое действие служит к показанию умоначертания действующих лиц; второе к продолжению умоначертания и к начатию <seg xml:lang="fr">sujet</seg>, о чем дело идет; третье—к продолжению <seg xml:lang="fr">sujet</seg>-а и к начатию, что называют амброглио
                <note type="editorial">
                    Catherine misspells (probably being influenced by French pronunciation) Italian word "imbroglio", which denounces an intricate or complicated situation in a play.
                </note>; четвертое— к амброглио; пятое—<seg xml:lang="fr">catastrophe</seg>, или окончание.
            <note type="editorial">
                <bibl>
                    <title ref="works.xml#sobstv02">Sobstvennoruchnyia pis'ma i zapiski imperatritsy Ekateriny II k A. V. Khranovitskomu, 1783-1793</title> (
                    <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 9.</biblScope>)
                </bibl>
                suggests that in this letter Catherine is writing about the opera <title ref="works.xml#feveyo01">"Fevey"</title>. According to A.V. Khrapovitskii's diary, <rs ref="works.xml#feveyo01"> this opera</rs> was first staged at <orgName ref="orgs.xml#impe01">Bolshoi Kamenny Theater</orgName> on <date when-custom="1786-04-19">April 19 1786</date>, then at the <placeName ref="places.xml#her01">Hermitage</placeName> on <date when-custom="1786-04-22">April 22 1786</date> (
                <bibl>
                    <title ref="works.xml#dnevni02">Dnevnik A.V. Khrapovitskago s 18 ianvaria 1782 po 17 sentiabria 1793 goda</title>
                    , <biblScope unit="pp">pp. 4.</biblScope>
                </bibl>
                ).
            </note>
            </p>
        </body>
